solution:
```class Solution {
    public int countSegments(String s) {
        if (s.trim().isEmpty()) {
            return 0;
        }
        return s.trim().split("\\s+").length;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses the trim() method to remove leading and trailing spaces, and then splits the string into segments using the split() method with a regular expression that matches one or more spaces. The length of the resulting array is the number of segments.

